column22: Are you currently pregnant?***Drinking alcohol at any time during pregnancy can cause serious harm to your developing baby. Alcohol consumption during pregnancy increases the chances of miscarriage and stillbirth and of premature birth low birthweight birth defects and fetal alcohol spectrum disorder in your baby.***Find more information about drinking during pregnancy here: https://www.marchofdimes.org/pregnancy/alcohol-during-pregnancy.aspxIf you need help to stop drinking you can: Talk to your healthcare provider about treatment programs. Join an Alcoholics Anonymous (AA) support group. In the United States: Use the SAMHSA Substance Abuse Treatment Facility Locator: https://findtreatment.samhsa.gov/ or call 1-800 662-4357.
